03/03/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police on Thursday (March 3rd) raided the houses of several people, including journalists and a former intelligence officer, as part of ongoing investigations into the so-called Ergenekon network, which is suspected of plans to topple the government. 
According to local reports, police searched computers, papers and books of the journalists, including Ahmet Sik, who already faces legal proceedings for co-authoring a book about the Ergenekon crackdown. 
(NTV, Milliyet, Hurriyet, CNN Turk - 03/03/11)
